The paper focuses on the communication practices and challenges of using animated GIFs, which are commonly used in text-based communication. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), which deals with the design, evaluation, and implementation of interactive computing systems for human use. Multimedia (cs.MM) is also a likely category, as the paper discusses the use of animated GIFs, which are a type of multimedia content. Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) is another possible category, as the paper examines the nuances of communication practices with GIFs. Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) are also possible categories, as the paper discusses the role of context and interpersonal relationships in the use and interpretation of GIFs.
